The '''Apostolic Nunciature to Savoy''' was an ecclesiastical office of the [[Catholic Church]] to the [[Duchy of Savoy]], [[Italy]].<ref name=CathHierNuncioSavoy>{{Cite web|last=Cheney |first=David M.|authorlink=|title=Nunciature to Savoy|publisher=''[[Catholic-Hierarchy.org]]''|date=|url=http://www.catholic-hierarchy.org/diocese/dx989.html  |accessdate=June 16, 2018}} [[Wikipedia:SPS|{{sup|[''self-published'']}}]]</ref> It was a diplomatic post of the [[Holy See]], whose representative is called the [[Apostolic Nuncio]] with the rank of an [[ambassador]]. The office ceased to exist in 1795 soon after the Duchy of Savoy was occupied by French revolutionary forces in 1792 after the [[French Revolution]] .

