The '''Jabuka-Andrija Fault''' is a seismically active [[thrust fault]] under the [[Adriatic Sea]] in [[Croatia]].<ref name="Ivančić2006">{{cite journal|last1=Ivančić|first1=Ines|last2=Herak|first2=Davorka|last3=Markušić|first3=Snježana|last4=Sović|first4=Ivica|last5=Herak|first5=Marijan|title=Seismicity of Croatia in the period 2002–2005|url=http://hrcak.srce.hr/index.php?lang=en&show=clanak&id_clanak_jezik=25740|journal=Geofizika|date=2006|volume=23|issue=2|accessdate=9 August 2014}}</ref> A series of earthquakes near [[Jabuka (island)|Jabuka island]], the strongest reaching a magnitude of 5.5, was caused by movements along the Jabuka-Andrija Fault.<ref name=Herak2005>{{cite journal|last1=Herak|first1=Davorka|last2=Herak|first2=Marijan|last3=Prelogović|first3=Eduard|last4=Markušić|first4=Snježana|last5=Markulin|first5=Željko|title=Jabuka island (Central Adriatic Sea) earthquakes of 2003|journal=Tectonophysics|volume=398|issue=3–4|pages=167–180|doi=10.1016/j.tecto.2005.01.007}}</ref>

