The '''Movement for the National Independence of Angola''' (in [[Portuguese language|Portuguese]]: ''Movimento para a Independência Nacional de Angola'') was a [[political party]] in [[Angola]], formed in 1958. MINA later merged with other parties to form the Popular Movement for the Liberation of Angola ([[MPLA]]).

