The '''Roman Catholic Diocese of Nnewi''' ({{lang-la|Nnevien(sis)}}) is a [[diocese]] located in the city of [[Nnewi]] in the [[Ecclesiastical province]] of [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Onitsha|Onitsha]] in [[Nigeria]].
==History== * November 28, 2001: Established as Diocese of Nnewi from the Metropolitan Archdiocese of Onitsha<ref>[http://www.nnewidiocese.org/diocese.htm Overview of the Diocese of Nnewi on the official website]</ref>
==Special churches== The [[Cathedral]] is Cathedral of Our Lady of Assumption in Nnewi.
==Leadership== * [[Bishop]]s of Nnewi (Roman rite) ** Bishop [[Hilary Paul Odili Okeke]] (since November 9, 2001)
==See also== *[http://www.nnewidiocese.org/diocese.htm www.nnewidiocese.org information page] *[[Roman Catholicism in Nigeria]]
