{{Infobox Union |name= Polisförbundet |country= [[Sweden]] |affiliation= [[Swedish Confederation of Professional Employees|TCO]], [[European Confederation of Police|EuroCOP]] |members= 18,500 |full_name= Swedish Police Union |native_name= |image= [[Image:Polisforbundet logo.png]] |founded= 1903 |current= |head= |dissolved_date= |dissolved_state= |merged_into= |office= [[Stockholm]], Sweden |people= [[Jan Karlsen]], president |website= [http://www.polisforbundet.se www.polisforbundet.se] |footnotes= }} <!-- Include all unused fields for future use. See [[template talk:Infobox Union]] for usage. -->
The '''Swedish Police Union''' (Polisförbundet) is a [[trade union]] in [[Sweden]]. It has a membership of 18,500 (including police academy students), and is affiliated with the [[Swedish Confederation of Professional Employees]], and [[EuroCOP]]. It also maintains contact with the Swedish branch of the [[International Police Association]].
==External links== * [http://www.polisforbundet.se Polisförbundet] official site.
